"Take the girl"?

01:38.399 --> 01:39.231
Don't argue with them.
Just go.

01:39.233 --> 01:41.300
- You better go with them.
- But they're not trying
to take me anywhere!

01:41.302 --> 01:43.735
Don't try to be a hero.
Do what they say!
They're not saying anything.

01:43.737 --> 01:47.439
Well, what's the sense?
If you keep arguing with them,
then we're all gonna die!

01:47.441 --> 01:48.807
- We don't want the girl!
- Then take the cash.

01:48.809 --> 01:52.744
- We don't want the cash!
- Well, then what the hell
do you want?

01:56.883 --> 02:00.185
We're takin'
you bitches hostage.

02:00.954 --> 02:04.623
♪ ♪

02:32.318 --> 02:35.787
That's right, and we need
a gassed-up boat, and we need
100,000 clams in a briefcase.

02:35.789 --> 02:40.959
And a--
And a Planet Hollywood jacket.
A leather one, reversible.

02:40.961 --> 02:43.462
[ Quietly ]
And we need a-a reversible
Planet Hollywood jacket too.

02:43.464 --> 02:46.899
Can't believe this is happening.
Taken hostage by the McPoyles.
We should just bum-rush 'em.

02:46.901 --> 02:50.769
Hey, I'm the one making
the demands here, pig!
If they're not met in one hour,

02:50.771 --> 02:53.305
I'm gonna kill
one of the hostages!

02:53.307 --> 02:56.375
You hear that, in one hour,
we're gonna have Margaret
shoot one of you in the face.

02:56.377 --> 03:00.345
And if any of you try to escape,
we'll massacre you
in a blaze of glory,

03:00.347 --> 03:03.215
then play
with your bodies.
Especially Dennis.

03:03.716 --> 03:06.485
Let's secure
the perimeter.

03:10.924 --> 03:13.358
Holy shit, did you hear that?
I think he means it.

03:13.360 --> 03:14.493
There's no way they're gonna
get those demands.

03:14.495 --> 03:16.595
They can't get a Planet
Hollywood jacket, those places
don't even exist anymore.

03:16.597 --> 03:20.732
They don't make those jackets.
They'd have to call Stallone,
and he's not gonna give his up.

03:20.734 --> 03:23.468
Maybe Aykroyd.
[ All Chattering, Overlapping ]

03:23.470 --> 03:25.671
Shut up!
We need to focus, okay?

03:25.673 --> 03:29.474
This is serious.
We could get Stockholm syndrome.
[ Gasps ]

03:29.476 --> 03:30.909
Oh, my God, what is that?
What is that?

03:30.911 --> 03:32.077
Does that start
with a sore throat?

03:32.079 --> 03:33.378
Because I think
I might be getting it.

03:33.380 --> 03:34.379
No, you're not getting it,
Charlie.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.682
Oh, I'm sorry, are you a doctor?
I don't think you're
qualified to tell me

03:36.684 --> 03:38.350
whether or not I'm coming
down with Stockholm syndrome?

03:38.352 --> 03:41.019
Stockholm syndrome, it--
it messes with your mind.

03:41.021 --> 03:43.722
You start to empathize and then
side with your captors.

03:43.724 --> 03:44.423
We could
turn against each other.

03:44.425 --> 03:47.059
No, Dee is right.
Now look, we need to watch out
for each other, okay?

03:47.061 --> 03:50.462
The only way we're gonna
get through this is
if we stick together.

03:50.464 --> 03:52.965
Nobody has to die.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.534
Somebody has to die.
Oh, yeah.

03:55.536 --> 03:56.969
Doesn't have to be one of us.
No, it shouldn't be.

03:56.971 --> 03:59.271
Mac or Charlie, right?
I mean, what do they
have to live for?

03:59.273 --> 04:00.372
Not one thing.

04:00.374 --> 04:03.775
