11:44.404 --> 11:47.205
Must be miserable
up in those vents,
Frank.

11:47.207 --> 11:50.041
- Charlie, is that you?
- Yeah, it's me.

11:50.043 --> 11:54.312
Hey, are you lost?
I warned you never to go up
in those vents without me.

11:54.314 --> 11:57.749
Uh, yeah, a little bit.
Hey, Charlie,

11:57.751 --> 12:01.152
you think you could
give the walkie-talkie
over to Mac?

12:01.154 --> 12:03.321
I gotta talk to him
privately.

12:03.323 --> 12:05.924
Yeah, hold on a second.

12:06.158 --> 12:10.462
- Yo, buddy, I'm here.
- Mac, go somewhere
where you're alone.

12:10.464 --> 12:13.231
[ Chuckles ]
[ Scoffs ]

12:13.233 --> 12:14.532
Okay, Frank,
we're alone.

12:14.534 --> 12:21.139
Whatever happens,
make sure Charlie's
the first one to die.

12:22.141 --> 12:25.110
- What, why?
- Because of this will business.

12:25.112 --> 12:26.911
He stands to gain
the most out of it.

12:26.913 --> 12:29.814
That's a very good point.
That's an excellent point.
All right.

12:29.816 --> 12:33.151
Uh, that's a good plan, Frank.
I'll get back to you
in about 10.

12:33.153 --> 12:34.986
A-All right,
get back to me, 10-4.

12:34.988 --> 12:39.457
Okay, well, I think it's
pretty clear what we should do.
Frank has to die.

12:39.459 --> 12:40.992
Gotta kill Frank.
Gotta kill him somehow.

12:40.994 --> 12:43.128
So once the McPoyles
take out Dennis, Dee and Frank--
Yeah.

12:43.130 --> 12:45.396
then you and I
will split the money
right down the middle.

12:45.398 --> 12:48.433
Ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh.
That's kind of a lot,
don't you think?

12:48.435 --> 12:51.469
I'll tell you what.
I'll give you 25%.
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

12:51.471 --> 12:54.272
<i>[ Mac ]</i>
<i>Twenty-five percent, Charlie--</i>
<i>It's my money, dude!</i>

12:54.274 --> 12:57.408
<i>Hey, ball sacks,</i>
<i>put those on.</i>
Why?

12:57.410 --> 13:02.013
It's too obvious
who the hostages
and who the captors are.

13:02.015 --> 13:04.783
We're gonna confuse
the cops.

13:08.220 --> 13:10.588
[ All Breathing Heavily ]

13:10.590 --> 13:12.857
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Your time is almost up.</i>

13:12.859 --> 13:14.526
And we thought
we'd spice things up
with an immunity challenge.

13:14.528 --> 13:18.163
The team who wins will be
exempt from the first round
of shootings in the face.

13:18.165 --> 13:20.565
Oh, well, that's
a great idea.
Dee, shut up.

13:20.567 --> 13:23.001
What the hell
is she talking about?
She's got Stockholm syndrome.

13:23.003 --> 13:28.339
No, I don't, no!
I just think it's a good way
to decide who to kill first.

13:28.341 --> 13:30.909
I'm tryin' to put myself
in their position, you know?

13:30.911 --> 13:31.943
It's called compassion,
dickheads.

13:31.945 --> 13:36.047
Maybe if you guys had a little
bit of it, you wouldn't be
in this mess in the first place,

13:36.049 --> 13:40.318
and then we wouldn't be standing
here tryin' to figure out which
one of you we have to kill.

13:40.320 --> 13:43.421
But that's where we are.
So hand me that shotgun--
[ Cocks ]

13:43.423 --> 13:45.890
'cause I'd like to do
this mess myself.

13:45.892 --> 13:47.659
Get on your knees, bitches!

13:47.661 --> 13:49.928
What are you doing?
Now you're on their side?

13:49.930 --> 13:52.564
You wanna be a McPoyle,
trash bag?
Huh?

13:52.566 --> 13:53.932
Mmm!
[ Gasps ]

13:53.934 --> 13:57.468
If you wanna be a McPoyle,
you've gotta earn that
the hard way.

13:57.470 --> 14:00.338
And you will learn that
later on, but for now,
the challenge is this:

14:00.340 --> 14:05.210
Whoever can destroy more things
on the inside of this bar wins.
And the teams have changed.

14:05.212 --> 14:07.512
It's now Dee and Charlie
versus Mac and Dennis.

14:07.514 --> 14:10.915
You have one minute
to plan your strategy...

14:10.917 --> 14:12.183
starting now.

14:12.185 --> 14:14.986
Whoop, come on.
Come here, come here, come here!

14:14.988 --> 14:16.855
I think I got a plan
to get us out of this.

14:16.857 --> 14:19.390
But I need you to do
the destroying thing.
Can you do that?

14:19.392 --> 14:20.358
No problem,
I'm a great destroyer.

14:20.360 --> 14:23.394
Are you kidding me, dude?
You're a born smasher.
Yes! I'm a born smasher.

14:23.396 --> 14:26.064
I'm gonna work a different angle
with the girl.
Work those pecs.

14:26.066 --> 14:29.667
Yeah, exactly, bump it.
All right, dude.
Dennis.

14:29.669 --> 14:31.970
What?
I love you.

14:31.972 --> 14:33.137
Go!
Go!
Go!

14:33.139 --> 14:34.706
Okay, okay, I got
a plan actually, okay?
Okay.

14:34.708 --> 14:37.375
I'm gonna start by wrecking
the back office, I don't think
anyone thought of that.

14:37.377 --> 14:39.978
The back office, Charlie, I feel
like there's a lot more stuff--
Hey!

14:39.980 --> 14:43.281
Listen to me, okay?
I don't blame you for that
betrayal but you're acting nuts.

14:43.283 --> 14:45.884
All right, listen.
I'm sorry about
that whole thing--

14:45.886 --> 14:47.652
Hey shut up, okay?
I'm tryin' to save
your life here, Dee.

14:47.654 --> 14:51.656
Listen, I'm gonna save your life
by wreckin' that back office.
We gotta stick together, okay?

14:51.658 --> 14:53.625
You got it?
Yes, I got it, Charlie.

14:53.627 --> 14:56.928
Time's up, assholes.
Start smashing!

14:56.930 --> 14:59.163
Mm.
Mmm.

14:59.165 --> 15:01.499
I love you.

15:02.234 --> 15:04.168
<i>[ Yells ]</i>

15:04.170 --> 15:07.639
[ Wheezing, Grunting ]

15:09.208 --> 15:15.480
Decided to come in here and take
a break from all the excitement.
It's got me all sweaty.

15:15.482 --> 15:18.349
So sweaty.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.618
Do you mind?

15:22.221 --> 15:25.757
Margaret,
you like sweat,
don't you?

15:25.759 --> 15:29.661
It is "Margaret,"
isn't it?
Of course, it is.

15:29.663 --> 15:33.197
You know, your eyebrow--
It drives me crazy.

15:33.199 --> 15:36.935
It's so thick.
It's so... dark...

15:36.937 --> 15:39.237
and so very...

15:40.272 --> 15:42.440
connected.

15:42.442 --> 15:44.475
You're a stone cold fox,
Margaret.

15:44.477 --> 15:47.211
You're a stone cold fox,
and I want you.

15:47.213 --> 15:49.580
I gotta have you.
I need you.

15:49.582 --> 15:51.683
I want you inside me.

15:51.685 --> 15:56.955
But you know that--
[ Whispering ]
don't you, Margaret?

15:56.957 --> 15:58.623
[ Slurps ]

15:58.625 --> 16:00.258
[ Quietly ]
Yeah.

16:00.260 --> 16:03.261
Look at yourself, Dee.
You've turned into a monster.

16:03.263 --> 16:04.595
Huh?
Not my fault.
I'm sick.

16:04.597 --> 16:08.433
I know, Dee, I know.
You're the one that first told
us about Stockholm syndrome.

16:08.435 --> 16:09.767
But I feel like,
if you just snap out it,

16:09.769 --> 16:12.603
there's a chance
that we could survive this,
if we just stick together.

16:12.605 --> 16:17.275
Whoa, all right, time's up.
Looks like Mac
and Dennis take it.

16:17.277 --> 16:18.309
Nice!
Blast away, boys.

16:18.311 --> 16:23.414
No, No, wait.
Wait, because Charlie--
Charlie destroyed the office!

16:23.416 --> 16:26.751
Go by and look.
Charlie saved my life!
[ Mac ] No. No, blast her!

16:26.753 --> 16:29.220
Charlie, we did it!
Blast her!
Damn it.

16:29.222 --> 16:31.489
We did it!

16:32.424 --> 16:34.759
[ Creaking ]

16:34.761 --> 16:38.629
Goddamn it, Charlie.

16:40.099 --> 16:42.600
<i>[ Mac On Walkie-Talkie ]</i>
<i>Frank, Frank.</i>
<i>Come in, Frank.</i>

16:42.602 --> 16:44.736
Oh, when we get outta this,

16:44.738 --> 16:49.440
I am gonna shove my fist
right into your ass,
hard and fast--

16:49.442 --> 16:53.311
not in a sexual way--
in a "I am pissed off
at you" way...

16:53.313 --> 16:56.481
for turnin' off
your walkie-talkie and
leavin' me in this shit hole!

16:56.483 --> 17:00.518
Listen to me very carefully,
Frank, Charlie has escaped.
Repeat, Charlie has escaped.

17:00.520 --> 17:03.388
- I think he's gonna
come after you, man.
- Don't worry about it.

17:03.390 --> 17:05.289
I can take care of myself. Ah!
<i>[ Glass Crunches ]</i>

17:05.291 --> 17:10.628
God, I just stepped in glass!
There's broken bottles
all over the place.

17:10.630 --> 17:12.663
Broken bottles
everywhere?
Oh, shit, dude.

17:12.665 --> 17:17.035
I think you're
in Charlie's "bad room."
What the hell is that?

17:17.037 --> 17:19.804
It's where he goes to be alone
and break bottles.

17:19.806 --> 17:23.141
Dude, you gotta be real careful.
He's gonna find you.

17:23.143 --> 17:25.410
I can take care of myself.

17:25.412 --> 17:28.112
<i>Hello, Frank.</i>

17:28.514 --> 17:30.381
I gotta call you back.

17:30.383 --> 17:33.551
Be careful.
Be careful.
H-Hi, Charlie.

17:34.119 --> 17:36.387
Lookin' for your will, Pop?

17:36.389 --> 17:37.488
That's exactly
what I'm lookin' for.

17:37.490 --> 17:43.361
You know, it's funny
what kind of men we turn into
in circumstances like this.

17:43.363 --> 17:45.530
I heard who you wanted
to have killed.

17:45.532 --> 17:48.132
But that goddamn Mac, he--

17:48.134 --> 17:52.804
Then tell me, Frank.
What do you think about...

17:54.873 --> 17:55.273
this?

17:55.275 --> 17:59.310
I like that very much.
That's exactly
why I came up here.

17:59.312 --> 18:01.212
No, it's the--
Oh, yeah, I guess it is.

18:01.214 --> 18:05.383
- Now let's get
the hell outta here.
- No, I don't think so, Frank!

18:05.385 --> 18:07.285
You see,
I don't need you anymore,
now do I?

18:07.287 --> 18:12.457
What are you talkin' about?
What are you doin'?
Put your hands down.

18:12.459 --> 18:14.926
Yeah, Yeah.
Charlie,
put your hands down.

18:14.928 --> 18:15.660
Charlie, don't--
Bye, Dad!

18:15.662 --> 18:18.529
Oh, my God, do you carry that
everywhere now, dude?
That's ridiculous.

18:18.531 --> 18:21.732
- Lead me the hell outta here.
- All right, fine.

18:21.734 --> 18:23.267
How?
This way.

18:23.269 --> 18:24.435
That way?
Put the gun--
[ Mutters ]

18:24.437 --> 18:27.705
I was gonna go<i> that</i> way.
No, that would've
been all wrong.

18:31.510 --> 18:33.711
All right, that was, uh--
[ Smacks Lips ]
nice.

18:33.713 --> 18:36.814
That was very...
hot and sweaty
and passionate--

18:36.816 --> 18:38.916
milky.
[ Clears Throat ]

18:38.918 --> 18:39.517
Now let's get outta here.

18:39.519 --> 18:41.586
Let's sneak outta here,
you know,
and start a life together.

18:41.588 --> 18:44.522
Let's get outta
this crazy place together.
Come on, let's go, sneak me out.

18:44.524 --> 18:47.558
What, Wha-- No.
No-no-no-no-no, no, we're done
with the kissing part, okay?

18:47.560 --> 18:50.761
That' part's over.
We're in love now, and you
can sneak me out of here.

18:50.763 --> 18:52.730
We're at that part now,
all right?
No, no-no-no.

18:52.732 --> 18:55.867
Oh, God, please tell me you
understand what I'm saying.
Do you understand me?

18:55.869 --> 18:58.669
Do you understand?
You don't understand, do you?
This has all been for nothing.

18:58.671 --> 19:02.473
- What the hell
is goin' on here?
- Uh, nothing.

19:02.475 --> 19:06.777
Doesn't look like nothing.
But for the record,
I'm into it.

19:06.779 --> 19:09.547
Everybody to the roof.
It's time to pay the piper.

19:09.549 --> 19:13.351
A couple of hundred more yards
and we're outta here.
A couple of hundred more yards?

19:13.353 --> 19:16.420
That's it, push!
[ Strains ]
[ Muttering ]

19:16.422 --> 19:18.589
Go!
[ Strains ]
We're, like, in a tomb, Charlie.

19:18.591 --> 19:22.994
I'm one of you guys, though.
I'm-- I'm a McPoyle now,
so you wouldn't kill me, right?

19:22.996 --> 19:24.128
No, she's got
Stockholm syndrome.

19:24.130 --> 19:25.329
Don't listen to her, okay?
She'll betray you.

19:25.331 --> 19:28.132
I'm the one that won
the immunity challenge--
I'm the one that should live.

19:28.134 --> 19:29.500
<i>Actually, we both won the</i>
<i>immunity challenge</i>

19:29.502 --> 19:31.169
<i>'cause we were on</i>
<i>the same team.</i>
<i>So we're both safe.</i>

19:31.171 --> 19:33.504
No, I did all the work.
You were in the bathroom
getting laid.

19:33.506 --> 19:35.339
He was getting laid.
I-- I love inbreeding!

19:35.341 --> 19:37.375
I like men in tight,
white underpants.
Uh--

19:37.377 --> 19:39.810
Get on your knees!
<i>[ Mac ]</i>
<i>Goddamn it!</i>

19:39.812 --> 19:42.480
[ Both Yelping, Grunting ]

19:42.482 --> 19:44.649
<i>We're free, dude!</i>
<i>We're free!</i>

19:44.651 --> 19:46.918
Frank and Charlie!
Frank and Charlie
came to save us!

19:46.920 --> 19:50.354
-<i> They're gonna save us!</i>
- [ Both Groaning, Panting ]

19:50.356 --> 19:54.659
- Right?
- [ Both Panting, Stop ]

19:56.929 --> 19:58.596
Uh, yeah.
Yeah.
Yeah, okay.

19:58.598 --> 20:03.167
- We came to save you.
- Yeah, yeah, we came here
to, uh, save you guys, yeah.

20:03.169 --> 20:04.569
<i>-That's exactly it,</i>
<i>why we came.</i>

20:04.571 --> 20:07.371
-No, we came to, uh,
save you, so here we are.

20:07.373 --> 20:08.940
Frank.

20:08.942 --> 20:11.309
Liam.

20:11.311 --> 20:13.644
What a delicious surprise.

20:13.646 --> 20:17.515
Looks like we got ourselves
into a bit of a pickle here.

20:17.517 --> 20:19.884
Get over
with your friends.

20:19.886 --> 20:22.019
I don't think so.

20:22.021 --> 20:24.455
- Really?
- Really.

20:24.457 --> 20:26.457
[ Chuckling ]

20:26.459 --> 20:29.293
[ Both Chuckling ]

20:29.295 --> 20:32.396
[ All Laughing ]

20:32.398 --> 20:36.367
[ All Laughing Louder,
Cackling ]

20:38.904 --> 20:42.440
<i>[ Laughing, Cackling Continue ]</i>

20:43.508 --> 20:46.477
Yippie-kay-yay, Mr. Fuckin'--

20:50.349 --> 20:52.550
<i>[ Gunfire Continues ]</i>

20:53.352 --> 20:59.357
[ Slowed Down ]
Brother!

20:59.359 --> 21:01.659
God, ah!
[ Whimpering ]

21:01.661 --> 21:03.894
Ah, I love you!
God, I love you!

21:03.896 --> 21:05.930
Hang on!
Ow!
Don't let go!

21:05.932 --> 21:09.267
I got you!
I got you, brother.

21:09.269 --> 21:10.768
Oh, no, you don't!

21:10.770 --> 21:13.804
Whoa!
What are you doing?
Ow, stop!

21:14.740 --> 21:17.775
Why are you doin' that?
[ Screams ]

21:19.745 --> 21:22.013
[ No Audible Scream ]

21:22.015 --> 21:27.785
[ Slowed Down ]
No-o-o!

21:27.787 --> 21:32.790
[ Laughing, Slowed Down ]

21:32.792 --> 21:34.492
[ Short Grunt ]

21:34.494 --> 21:38.396
- [ Liam ] Are you all right?
- Yeah, think I might get
a bruise on my heel.

21:38.398 --> 21:42.733
-That's not bad.
-No, it's not really bad at all.
It's pretty fun, it's like, ah!

21:42.735 --> 21:46.404
Why don't you guys climb
down that ladder?
[ Liam ] All right.

21:46.406 --> 21:47.571
Later, bitches.

21:47.573 --> 21:49.840
"Later, bitches"?
What, wait.
So they're just leaving?

21:49.842 --> 21:51.642
Why are they leaving?
What is
happening here?

21:51.644 --> 21:54.779
[ Dee ] This gun is rubber.
Rubber gun!
[ Mac ] It's rubber?

21:54.781 --> 21:57.448
She's right.
It's rubber.
There's no police!

21:57.450 --> 21:59.817
There's no police
down there, dude!
What the hell is happening?

21:59.819 --> 22:02.153
What is
going on here?
Are they just screwin' with us?

22:02.155 --> 22:03.788
Where are the cops?
<i>[ Ryan ]</i>
<i>Ha-ha!</i>

22:03.790 --> 22:07.892
Revenge, we got you, suckers!
Nobody messes
with the McPoyles!

22:07.894 --> 22:11.395
Whoo!
Ha-ha!
Eat it, douche bags!

22:11.397 --> 22:13.531
<i>[ Both Hooting In Distance ]</i>

22:13.533 --> 22:18.502
[ Liam ]
Whoo!
Whoo, McPoyles!

22:18.504 --> 22:21.672
Goddamn it!

22:21.674 --> 22:25.576
♪ ♪

22:54.639 --> 22:58.142
<i>[ Voices Speaking Backwards ]</i>
